<item>
            <title>[LU-16705] don&apos;t prolong client side locks for lockless/server locked IO</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16705</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the client sends a read or write RPC to the server, it informs the server which lock covers the IO, so that lock can be prolonged.&#160; But for server side locked IO, this is wrong.&#160; The lock will not be used and prolonging it delays the IO, occasionally leading to evictions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="75403">LU-16705</key>
